dcterms:description: The CETO 6 Wave Energy Converter (WEC) system is a complex device designed to optimize energy capture efficiency and reduce structural stress in challenging ocean conditions.
dcterms:title: CETO 6 Wave Energy Converter (WEC) system

dcterms:description: Wave data collected from various locations including Albany, Garden Island in Western Australia, Armintza in Spain, Biscay Marine Energy Platform, and Wave Hub on the north coast of Cornwall in the United Kingdom.
dcterms:title: Wave Data from Multiple Locations

dcterms:description: The Jonswap spectrum is used for modeling wave generation in simulations, representing the energy distribution of ocean waves.
dcterms:title: Jonswap Spectrum

dcterms:description: Data on principal wave periods and heights used for evaluating the performance of the wave energy converter.
dcterms:title: Principal Wave Periods and Heights

dcterms:description: Energy capture data generated from the reinforcement learning controller used to optimize the performance of the wave energy converter.
dcterms:title: Energy Capture Data from RL Controller
